<inglise> ANNEX </inglise>
<eesti> LISA </eesti>
<inglise> SECTION I </inglise>
<eesti> I JAGU </eesti>
<inglise> Definition of'subcontract' </inglise>
<eesti> Allhankelepingu m&auml;&auml;ratlus </eesti>
<inglise> 'Subcontract' means a contract concluded by an undertaking (hereinafter called the'principal contractor') with another undertaking (hereinafter called the'subcontractor') under which it is agreed that, in performance of another contract made between the principal contractor and a third undertaking (hereinafter called the'buyer'), the subcontractor will deliver goods or perform services which the principal contractor must incorporate or use in supplying the item or items which the buyer has ordered from him, it being understood that: </inglise>
<eesti> Allhankelepinguks nimetatakse ettev&otilde;tja (edaspidi "peat&ouml;&ouml;ettev&otilde;tja") poolt teise ettev&otilde;tjaga (edaspidi "allhankija") s&otilde;lmitavat lepingut, milles lepitakse kokku, et peat&ouml;&ouml;ettev&otilde;tja poolt kolmanda ettev&otilde;tjaga (edaspidi "ostja") s&otilde;lmitava lepingu t&auml;itmiseks tarnib allhankija kaupu ja osutab teenuseid, mida peat&ouml;&ouml;ettev&otilde;tja peab lisama ostja poolt tellitud kaubale v&otilde;i kaupadele v&otilde;i kasutama nende hankimisel, v&otilde;ttes arvesse j&auml;rgmisi tingimusi: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) Position in law </inglise>
<eesti> a) &Otilde;iguslik seisund </eesti>
<inglise> The subcontractor is not a co-signatory to the contract concluded between the principal contractor and the buyer, and the principal contractor has sole responsibility to the buyer for performance of the contract and bears all the risks which may be guaranteed in relation to the latter. </inglise>
<eesti> Allhankija ei ole peat&ouml;&ouml;ettev&otilde;tja ja ostja vahel s&otilde;lmitava lepingu kaasallakirjutaja, ja peat&ouml;&ouml;ettev&otilde;tja vastutab ostja ees lepingu t&auml;itmise eest ainuisikuliselt ja kannab k&otilde;iki riskid, mida sellega seoses on v&otilde;imalik kindlustada. </eesti>
<inglise> (b) Technical and economic position </inglise>
<eesti> b) Tehniline ja majanduslik seisund </eesti>
<inglise> Supplies from the subcontractor cover goods (other than raw materials or semi-finished goods) and/or services which, from the technical and economic point of view, consitute for the buyer essential ancillaries to performance of the contract by the principal contractor. </inglise>
<eesti> Allhankija tarned h&otilde;lmavad kaupu (v&auml;lja arvatud tooraine ja pooltooted) ja/v&otilde;i teenuseid, mis tehnilisest v&otilde;i majanduslikust seisukohast on ostjale h&auml;davajalikud lepingu t&auml;itmiseks peat&ouml;&ouml;ettev&otilde;tja poolt. </eesti>
<inglise> SECTION II </inglise>
<eesti> II JAGU </eesti>
<inglise> Automatic inclusion of subcontracts in the cover </inglise>
<eesti> Allhankelepingute automaatne kindlustuskate </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Subcontracts exclusively with parties in one or more Member States shall be automatically included in the cover which may be granted to the principal contractor where the amount of such subcontracts is equal to or less than: </inglise>
<eesti> Allhankelepingutele, mis s&otilde;lmitakse eranditult &uuml;hest v&otilde;i mitmest liikmesriigist p&auml;rit isikuga, antakse automaatselt kindlustuskate, mida v&otilde;ib peat&ouml;&ouml;ettev&otilde;tjale anda, kui allhankelepingu v&auml;&auml;rtus on v&otilde;rdne v&otilde;i v&auml;iksem kui: </eesti>
<inglise> - 40 % for contracts of a value less than 7 500 000 ECU, </inglise>
<eesti> - 40% lepingute korral, mille v&auml;&auml;rtus on alla 7 500 000 ek&uuml;&uuml;, </eesti>
<inglise> - 3 000 000 ECU for contracts of a value between 7 500 000 and 10 000 000 ECU, </inglise>
<eesti> - 3 000 000 ek&uuml;&uuml;d lepingute korral, mille v&auml;&auml;rtus on 7 500 000-10 000 000 ek&uuml;&uuml;d, </eesti>
<inglise> - 30 % for contracts of a value over 10 000 000 ECU. </inglise>
<eesti> - 30% lepingute korral, mille v&auml;&auml;rtus on &uuml;le 10 000 000 ek&uuml;&uuml;. </eesti>
<inglise> However, where the principal contractor's credit insurer is unable, because the risk inherent in the transaction is particularly heavy, to support cover for the whole of the transaction, consultation between the interested credit insurance organizations shall take place with a view to resolving the problem by means of joint insurance or, if possible, re-insurance. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui peat&ouml;&ouml;ettev&otilde;tja krediidikindlustusandja ei suuda siiski tehinguga kaasneva suure riski t&otilde;ttu pakkuda kindlustuskatet kogu tehingule, konsulteerivad huvitatud krediidikindlustusorganisatsioonid omavahel, et lahendada probleem kaaskindlustuse v&otilde;i, v&otilde;imaluse korral, edasikindlustuse abil. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Where export contracts involve subcontracting both in Member States and in non-member countries, subcontracting in Member States shall be automatically included, in so far as total subcontracting in all countries does not exceed the percentages and limits fixed in paragraph 1 by reference to the value of the contract. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui ekspordilepingud h&otilde;lmavad allhankeid nii liikmesriikidest kui ka kolmandatest riikidest, antakse liikmesriikides toimuvatele allhangetele automaatselt kindlustuskate, kui k&otilde;ikide riikide allhangete kogumaksumus ei &uuml;leta lepingu v&auml;&auml;rtusega seoses l&otilde;ikes 1 kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud protsente ja piirsummasid. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Cover shall be granted to the principal contractor, under the same conditions, whether he has recourse to national subcontracting or to subcontracting in other Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> Peat&ouml;&ouml;ettev&otilde;tjale antakse kindlustuskate samadel tingimustel, olenemata sellest, kas ta kasutab siseriiklikke allhankeid v&otilde;i allhankeid teistest liikmesriikidest. </eesti>
<inglise> SECTION III </inglise>
<eesti> III JAGU </eesti>
<inglise> Financing of subcontracts which have been included in cover </inglise>
<eesti> Kindlustatud allhangete rahastamine </eesti>
<inglise> Without prejudice to application of the customary criteria used in banking matters, treatment equal to that applicable to export contracts comprising exclusively national supplies shall be granted, as regards financing, in respect of export contracts which include subcontracts incorporated in accordance with the provisions of Section II. </inglise>
<eesti> Ilma et see piiraks panganduses tavap&auml;rastelt kasutatavate kriteeriumide rakendamist, k&auml;sitletakse vastavalt II jao s&auml;tetele allhankelepinguid sisaldavaid ekspordilepinguid rahastamisel v&otilde;rdselt selliste ekspordilepingutega, mis sisaldavad eranditult siseriiklikke tarneid. </eesti>
<inglise> SECTION IV </inglise>
<eesti> IV JAGU </eesti>
<inglise> Exchange of information </inglise>
<eesti> Teabevahetus </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> A subsequent exchange of information shall take place within the framework of the Policy Coordination Group for Credit Insurance, Credit Guarantees and Financial Credits as regards individual contracts in respect of which subcontracting in non-member countries exceeds 30 % and, in respect of mixed subcontracting both in Member States and in non-member countries, where the total value exceeds that percentage. </inglise>
<eesti> Krediidikindlustuse, krediidigarantii ja finantskrediidipoliitika koordineerimisr&uuml;hmale teatatakse tagantj&auml;rele &uuml;ksiklepingutest, mille allhanked kolmandatest riikidest &uuml;letavad 30%, ning allhangetest, mis tehakse nii liikmesriikidest kui ka kolmandatest riikidest, kui nende koguv&auml;&auml;rtus &uuml;letab nimetatud protsendim&auml;&auml;ra. </eesti>
<inglise> Such exchange of information shall, however, only take place for individual contracts exceeding 500 000 ECU in value and involving credit for a period of more than three years. </inglise>
<eesti> See teave esitatakse ainult selliste &uuml;ksiklepingute kohta, mille v&auml;&auml;rtus on &uuml;le 500 000 ek&uuml;&uuml; ja krediidiaeg kolm aastat. </eesti>
<inglise> The following shall apply: </inglise>
<eesti> Sel juhul kehtib j&auml;rgmine kord: </eesti>
<inglise> - such individual contracts are to be considered as exceptional, </inglise>
<eesti> - selliseid &uuml;ksiklepinguid tuleb k&auml;sitleda erandina, </eesti>
<inglise> - a study may at any time be made within the Coordination Group of the difficulties which may arise in connection with certain individual contracts reported within the framework of the subsequent exchange of information, </inglise>
<eesti> - koordineerimisr&uuml;hm v&otilde;ib igal ajal uurida raskusi, mis v&otilde;ivad tekkida seoses teatavate &uuml;ksiklepingutega, millest on tagantj&auml;rele teatatud, </eesti>
<inglise> - if experience shows that the subsequent exchange of information procedure is unsatisfactory, the Commission and the Member States may request that ways and means be sought of remedying those aspects that are found to be unsatisfactory. </inglise>
<eesti> - kui kogemused n&auml;itavad, et tagantj&auml;rele toimuv teabevahetus ei ole piisav, v&otilde;ivad komisjon ja liikmesriigid taotleda, et otsitaks v&otilde;imalusi ja vahendeid leitud puuduste k&otilde;rvaldamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Where a Member State proposes to conclude with a non-member country an agreement relating to inclusion of subcontracts on a reciprocal basis, the Member State concerned shall submit a preliminary notification to be followed by consultations within the framework of the Policy Coordination Group for Credit Insurance, Credit Guarantees and Financial Credits. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui liikmesriik kavatseb s&otilde;lmida kolmanda riigiga vastastikkuse alusel allhankelepinguid sisaldava lepingu, teatab asjaomane liikmesriik sellest eelnevalt ja konsulteerib krediidikindlustuse, krediidigarantii ja finantskrediidipoliitika koordineerimisr&uuml;hmaga. </eesti>
<inglise> The percentages relating to automatic inclusion allowable in such agreements may not - unless the Council decides otherwise - exceed 30 % irrespective of whether the subcontracting is in the non-member country with which the agreement has been made or whether subcontracting in other countries is involved. </inglise>
<eesti> Automaatselt kindlustusega kaetav protsent, mis on selliste lepingute puhul lubatud, ei tohi, kui n&otilde;ukogu ei otsusta teisiti, &uuml;letada 30%, olenemata sellest, kas allhanked tehakse kolmandast riigist, kellega on leping s&otilde;lmitud, v&otilde;i teistest asjaomastest riikidest. </eesti>
<inglise> SECTION V </inglise>
<eesti> V JAGU </eesti>
<inglise> Basis of calculation </inglise>
<eesti> Arvutamise alus </eesti>
<inglise> The percentages and amounts referred to shall be calculated in accordance with the following rules: </inglise>
<eesti> Eespool osutatud protsendid ja summad arvutatakse vastavalt j&auml;rgmistele eeskirjadele: </eesti>
<inglise> - costs incidental to export i. e. transport and insurance, are included in the total amount of the contract on which these percentages and amounts are calculated, </inglise>
<eesti> - ekspordiga kaasnevad kulud ehk transpordi- ja kindlustuskulud kuuluvad lepingu kogusummasse, mille alusel need protsendid ja summad arvutatakse, </eesti>
<inglise> - financing costs are totally excluded from the amount of the contract, whether itemized or not, </inglise>
<eesti> - rahastamiskulud ei kuulu lepingu kogusummasse, olenemata sellest, kas need on eraldi v&auml;lja toodud v&otilde;i mitte, </eesti>
<inglise> - the non-repatriable portion of incidental local expenditure on supplies is not normally deducted from the amount of the contract, it being understood, however, that if this portion exceeds 15 % of the amount of the contract less the costs of financing, the excess will be deducted. </inglise>
<eesti> - tarnetega kaasnevate kohalike kulude osa, mida ei saa tagastada, ei lahutata tavaliselt lepingu kogusummast, v&otilde;ttes siiski arvesse, et kui see osa &uuml;letab 15% lepingu summast, millest on lahutatud rahastamiskulud, tuleb &uuml;lej&auml;&auml;nud osa maha arvata. </eesti>
 